-- U.S. Stocks Pare Gains as Apple Drags Down Technology Shares
-- B y   N i c k   B a k e r
-- 2012-04-24T18:34:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-24/u-s-stocks-pare-gains-as-apple-drags-down-technology-shares.html
U.S. stocks pared gains as
technology shares retreated, dragged down by  Apple Inc. (AAPL) ’s 10th
decline in 11 days as investors await the company’s quarterly
report after markets close today.  The Standard & Poor’s 500 Index rose 0.2 percent to
1,369.14 at 2:31 p.m. New York time, trimming its advance from
0.6 percent. Computer-related stocks in the index slumped 0.9
percent. Apple decreased 2.4 percent, extending its drop since
April 9 to 12 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Baker at 
 nbaker7@bloomberg.net  